history.content: Yes, IMO it would be better to drop and re-add. Being #1 on the lecture waitlist isn't going to help if you're #20 on discussion waitlist once seats are released.

children.subject: how do you check if the number you are on the discussion waitlist? I am number 149 in total :/ it has not been moving

history.content:
I am currently number 59 on the lecture waitlist for CS188 ( I am not a declared). Although my lecture position is relatively low, I am in a discussion section that only has 2 spots open and around 22 people on the discussion waitlist. I am fairly confident that I am not in position 1 or 2 for discussion waitlist.

My question is, is it in my interest to just stay where I am or should I drop and add to a discussion section which has more open seats than waitlisted people (there is at least one currently that works with my schedule). 

I realize dropping and then waitlisting again will move my lecture waitlist position much higher, but it would put me in a better discussion waitlist position. I have read quite a lot of past questions on here along these lines but there seems to be a lot of conflicting answers on discussion waitlist vs lecture waitlist.

Thanks for your time! :)
